---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import PageHero from '@/components/PageHero.astro';
import { SITE } from '@/data/site';
const crumbs=[{label:'Privacy policy'}];
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | AUNO Center" description="How AUNO Center collects, uses, protects, retains, and responds to requests concerning personal information submitted through this website." breadcrumbs={crumbs}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs}/><PageHero eyebrow="Legal & privacy" title="Privacy Policy" lead="AUNO Center respects your privacy and aims to collect only the information reasonably needed to operate this website, respond to enquiries, and provide agreed communications." tone="light" />
  <section class="section"><div class="shell legal-layout"><aside><div class="side-card"><h2>Policy details</h2><dl><dt>Effective date</dt><dd>11 July 2026</dd><dt>Contact</dt><dd><a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a></dd></dl></div><div class="notice notice--critical"><h2>Do not submit sensitive data</h2><p>Public forms are for initial, non-confidential enquiries only.</p></div></aside><article class="prose">
    <h2 class="mt-0">Information we may collect</h2><ul><li>Contact details such as name, email address, and preferred contact method.</li><li>Professional information such as role, institution, country or region, research area, learning goals, and relevant experience.</li><li>Information submitted through contact, research-support, training, course enrollment, scholarship, collaboration, professional-interest, or subscription forms.</li><li>An optional CV or résumé submitted through the professional-interest portal. These files are private form submissions and are not included in the public website repository.</li><li>Correspondence and records reasonably needed to respond to an enquiry or manage an agreed service.</li><li>Limited technical information such as browser type, approximate location derived from an IP address, access time, security logs, and protection against misuse.</li><li>Consent and communication preferences.</li></ul>
    <div class="callout"><p><strong>Please do not submit</strong> patient information, participant identifiers, private institutional records, passwords, financial credentials, confidential datasets, or other unnecessary sensitive information through public website forms.</p></div>
    <h2>How information is used</h2><p>Information may be used to respond to you, assess whether a request is within scope, prepare a proposal, administer an agreed service, manage training or events, send requested updates, maintain appropriate records, improve website usability, prevent abuse, and meet applicable legal obligations.</p>
    <h2>Legal grounds</h2><p>Where applicable, information may be processed with consent, to take steps you request before an agreement, to perform an agreement, to meet a legal obligation, or for legitimate interests such as communication, administration, service improvement, and website security. The applicable basis depends on context and jurisdiction.</p>
    <h2>Website forms and Netlify</h2><p>This website uses Netlify Forms to receive submissions. Form data may be processed and stored by the hosting provider so AUNO Center can review and respond. Do not use a public form for sensitive research records. Appropriate provider terms, project settings, access controls, notification destinations, and retention practices should be reviewed by the site administrator.</p>
    <h2>PubMed search and Interpeko</h2><p>When you submit a PubMed search, the public query is sent through an AUNO Center Netlify Function to the official NCBI E-utilities service. Do not include personal or confidential information in a literature query. Interpeko uses a limited approved knowledge map in your browser and does not send questions to an external artificial-intelligence provider. Questions are not submitted as website forms.</p>
    <h2>Sharing and service providers</h2><p>AUNO Center may use service providers for hosting, security, form delivery, communications, document handling, or other necessary operations. They should receive only the information needed for their function. Information may also be disclosed when required by law or reasonably needed to protect rights, safety, and security.</p><p>AUNO Center does not sell personal information.</p>
    <h2>International processing</h2><p>Website and communication providers may process information in more than one country. Appropriate contractual, organisational, and technical safeguards should be used where required by applicable law.</p>
    <h2>Retention</h2><p>Information is retained only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purpose collected, recordkeeping, dispute management, security, or applicable legal requirements, and is then deleted or anonymised where practicable. Netlify form submissions should be reviewed and deleted under an active retention practice rather than kept indefinitely.</p>
    <h2>Security</h2><p>Reasonable administrative and technical measures are used to protect information. No website, email system, or online transfer can be guaranteed completely secure. Sensitive project data should be exchanged only through a separately agreed and approved secure process.</p>
    <h2>Your choices and rights</h2><p>Depending on applicable law, you may ask to access, correct, delete, restrict, or receive a copy of personal information, object to certain processing, or withdraw consent. Send requests to <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>. Identity may need to be verified before a request is completed.</p>
    <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2><p>Essential technologies may be used for security and website operation. This version of the website does not intentionally load third-party advertising trackers or external analytics. Non-essential analytics, advertising, embeds, or tracking should not be activated without appropriate notice and consent where required.</p>
    <h2>External links</h2><p>Links to social platforms and other websites are provided for convenience. AUNO Center does not control and is not responsible for their privacy, security, content, or accessibility practices.</p>
    <h2>Children</h2><p>This website is not directed to children who cannot lawfully consent to the relevant processing in their jurisdiction. A parent, guardian, educator, or authorised institution should contact AUNO Center where appropriate.</p>
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2><p>This policy may be updated to reflect operational, legal, or technical changes. The effective date will be revised when material changes are published.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2><p>Privacy questions and requests may be sent to <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.</p>
  </article></div></section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>.legal-layout{display:grid;grid-template-columns:19rem minmax(0,48rem);gap:clamp(3rem,7vw,7rem);justify-content:center;align-items:start}.legal-layout>aside{position:sticky;top:1rem}.legal-layout .notice{margin-top:1rem}.legal-layout dl{margin-top:1rem}.legal-layout dt{color:var(--gold-dark);font-size:.7rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.legal-layout dd+dt{margin-top:1rem}@media(max-width:61.99rem){.legal-layout{grid-template-columns:1fr}.legal-layout>aside{position:static;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem}.legal-layout .notice{margin-top:0}}@media(max-width:47.99rem){.legal-layout>aside{grid-template-columns:1fr}}</style>
